{{Infobox writer | name = Amber Dermont | occupation = Writer, Associate Professor of English | nationality = American | alma_mater = [[University of Houston]] }} '''Amber Dermont''' is an American author. She has a bachelor's degree from [[Vassar College]], an MFA in fiction from the [[Iowa Writers' Workshop]] and a Ph.D. in Creative Writing and Literature from the [[University of Houston]], and she is a faculty member at [[Rice University]].<ref>[http://english.rice.edu/Dermont.aspx Rice Department of English], accessed September 9, 2014.</ref>
==Books== Dermont is the author of two books: ''The Starboard Sea'', a novel,<ref name="auto">[https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/04/books/review/the-starboard-sea-amber-dermonts-debut-novel.html "In Knots"], Eleanor Henderson, ''The New York Times'', March 1, 2012.</ref> and ''Damage Control'', a story collection.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2013/03/24/books/review/damage-control-by-amber-dermont.html "I've Been Meaning to Tell You"], Caitlin Macy, ''The New York Times'', March 22, 2013.</ref>
''The Starboard Sea'' is a novel about a boy who transfers to a new prep school after a tragedy involving his sailing partner.<ref name="auto"/><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/29/books/the-starboard-sea-a-novel-by-amber-dermont.html "A Young Man of Privilege in Deep Water"], Janet Maslin, ''The New York Times.</ref> The book was a [[The New York Times best seller list|''New York Times'' best seller]]<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2012-03-19/hardcover-fiction/list.html Hardcover Fiction], ''The New York Times'', March 19, 2012.</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2012-03-25/hardcover-fiction/list.html Hardcover Fiction], ''The New York Times'', March 25, 2012.</ref> and was named one of ''[[The New York Times]]''' 100 Notable Books of 2012.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/02/books/review/100-notable-books-of-2012.html "100 Notable Books of 2012"], ''The New York Times'', November 27, 2012.</ref> It was also a finalist for the 2014 [[Townsend Prize for Fiction]].<ref>[http://depts.gpc.edu/townsend/finalists.html 2014 Finalists], The Townsend Prize for Fiction, accessed September 9, 2014.</ref>
