{{Infobox laboratory | name = Princess Haya Biotechnology Center (PHBC) | image = [[File:PrincessHayaBiotech.png|100px]] | established = 2005 | director = Dr. Laith N Al-Eitan <ref name=s>{{cite web|url=http://www.just.edu.jo/eportfolio/Pages/Default.aspx?email=lneitan|title=Home|work=just.edu.jo}}</ref> | city = [[Ar Ramtha]], [[Jordan]] {{Flagicon|Jordan}} | budget = | type = Biotechnology, Public health, Pharmaceuticals, National security | staff = | campus = | operating_agency = <small>[[Jordan University of Science and Technology]] (JUST)</small> | website = [http://www.just.edu.jo/Centers/PrincessHayaBiotechnologyCenter/ JUST-PHBC] }}
The '''Princess Haya Biotechnology Center (PHBC)''' houses 16 research laboratories and supports scientific activity at the national and regional level. It was established at the [[Jordan University of Science and Technology]] (JUST) on the campus of [[King Abdullah University Hospital]] (KAUH) in 2005.<ref name=JUSTPHBC>{{cite web|url=http://www.just.edu.jo/Centers/PrincessHayaBiotechnologyCenter/Pages/vision_mission.aspx|title=Vision and Mission|work=just.edu.jo}}</ref> ٍDr. Laith Al-Eitan is the director of the center, [[Princess Haya bint Al Hussein|Princess Haya]] serves as Honorary President.<ref name=prhaya.net>{{cite web |url=http://www.princesshaya.net/health/princess-haya-biotechnology-centre |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-12-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130222082409/http://www.princesshaya.net/health/princess-haya-biotechnology-centre |archivedate=2013-02-22 |df= }}</ref>
As well as local cooperation with universities and hospitals in the country, the center has expanded its activity beyond the national borders, liaising with a forensic medicine institute in Iraq, the [[Saint Joseph University]] in Lebanon, the Hamdan Bin Rashid Organisation for Excellence in the UAE, the Human Genetics Center at the [[Humboldt University of Berlin|University of Humboldt]] in Germany, the Forensic Medicine Center at the [[University of Western Australia]],<ref name=JUSTPHBC/> and [[Sandia National Laboratories]] in the USA.<ref name=prhaya.net/>
